# Description: Headcount vs multi-qualification extreme case.
# Scenario: A1 requires 2x Q1. P1 has Q1, Q2, and Q3 and is the only person on the boat.
# Reasoning: For A1, the headcount requirement for Q1 cannot be satisfied since P1 contributes only once (binary presence),
# so 2x Q1 is infeasible. For A2, all required qualifications (Q1, Q2, Q3) are satisfied by P1 on the same boat.
# Expected result: A1 cannot be executed; A2 can be executed by P1 alone.
# Maximize WorkHours: 4.
data;
set TASKS := A1 A2;
set QUALIS := Q1 Q2 Q3;
set PEOPLE := P1;
set TOOLS := W1;

param amountBoats := 1;
param maxWorkingHours := 10;

param duration := A1 10 A2 4;

param hasQuali := 
P1 Q1 1
P1 Q2 1
P1 Q3 1;

param requiredQualis := 
A1 Q1 2 A1 Q2 0 A1 Q3 0
A2 Q1 1 A2 Q2 1 A2 Q3 1;

param requiredTools := A1 W1 0 A2 W1 0;
param stockTools := W1 0;
end;
